For every built-in color theme with Visual Studio Code, the assigned color for comments ... 

```
//Default Dark+ Theme
{
	"scope": "comment",
	"settings": {
		"foreground": "#608b4e"
	}
}
```
... is being overridden by keywords associated with documentation conventions (JSDoc, etc), such as...

```
//Default Dark+ Theme
{
	"scope": "storage.type",
	"settings": {
		"foreground": "#569cd6"
	}
}
```

Example:

![capture](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/933921/23041637/8b69b93e-f463-11e6-8b55-a3c05f63da54.PNG)

What key/value can be added to the theme files, either .json defaults or TextMate theme files, so that the color of comments remains intact.
